9. Develop and demonstrate, using JavaScript script, a XHTML document 
that contains three short paragraphs of text, stacked on top of each other, 
with only enough of each showing so that the mouse cursor can be placed over some part of them. 
When the cursor is placed over the exposed part of any paragraph, it should rise to the
top to become completely visible


<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Program 9</title>

    <style type="text/css">

    .layer1Style
    {
        border: solid thick black;
        padding: 1em;
        width:300px;
        background-color:yellow;
        position:absolute;
        top:100px;
        left:200px;
        z-index:0;
    }

    .layer2Style
    {
        border:solid thick red;
        padding:1em;
        width:300px;
        background-color:blue;
        color:white;
        position:absolute;
        top:120px;
        left:220px;
        z-index:0;
    }

    .layer3Style
    {
        border:solid thick green;
        padding:1em;
        width:300px;
        background-color:purple;
        color:white;
        position:absolute;
        top:140px;
        left:240px;
        z-index:0;
    }

    </style>

    <script type="text/javascript">

    var topLayer = "layer3";

    function mover(toTop)
    {
        var oldTop = document.getElementById(topLayer).style;
        var newTop = document.getElementById(toTop).style;

        oldTop.zIndex = "0";
        newTop.zIndex = "10";

        topLayer = document.getElementById(toTop).id;
    }

    </script>

</head>

<body>

<h2>Stacking of Paragraphs</h2>

<div class="layer1Style" id="layer1" style="z-index:10;"
     onmouseover="mover('layer1')">

This is a story about four people: Everybody, Somebody, Anybody, and Nobody.
There was an important job to be done and Everybody was asked to do it.
Everybody was sure Somebody would do it. Anybody could have done it, but
Nobody did it. Somebody got angry because it was Everybody's job.
Everybody thought Anybody could do it, but Nobody realized that Everybody
wouldn't do it.

</div>

<div class="layer2Style" id="layer2" style="z-index:2;"
     onmouseover="mover('layer2')">

Once upon a time, there lived a big lion in a jungle. Every day he hunted
many animals for food. The animals decided to find a solution and met the
lion. The lion agreed that one animal would come every day instead of
hunting all the animals.

</div>

<div class="layer3Style" id="layer3" style="z-index:0;"
     onmouseover="mover('layer3')">

One day a wolf found a sheepskin and wore it to enter a flock of sheep.
He planned to catch a sheep at night. But the shepherd's servant mistook
the wolf for a sheep and caught it instead. Thus, the wolf's evil plan
ended in failure.

</div>

</body>
</html>
